cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper discusses the design and implementation of a software framework for a multimodal interface that integrates hyperlink and speech modes of interaction. The focus is on web browsing, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of speech recognition technology suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The framework also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) components, as it enables the creation of websites that adapt to the needs of users and support multiple modes of interaction.
